{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:34:58.942832+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 876d622f0ff02008cb21be413cfd181dbcd7eb3d)", "id": "lc_418b1fae-1f62-4ac3-8775-abb871337e51"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Local Web Baseline Scan\n\nA local web security review project using OWASP ZAP baseline scanning against a demo application and sample report fixtures.\n\n## Project layout\n\n- `app.py` — Minimal local demo application.\n- `zap/` — Baseline scan configuration.\n- `sample_data/` — Sample ZAP baseline JSON.\n- `reports/` — Generated scan summaries.\n- `scripts/` — Baseline scan and report conversion helpers.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nmake validate\n```\n```bash\npython3 scripts/zap_json_to_markdown.py\n```\n\n## Baseline review workflow\n\n1. Run or inspect the local demo application.\n2. Review ZAP policy files before changing alert handling.\n3. Convert JSON outputs into Markdown summaries for review.\n4. Keep endpoint scope documentation current.\n\nThe scan helper is scoped to local demo targets.\n\n## Maintenance notes\n\nThe ZAP runner only allows localhost, 127.0.0.1, or host.docker.internal targets.\n\n## Contributing\n\nKeep changes focused, update documentation when behavior changes, and run the validation commands before submitting a pull request.\n", "id": "lc_287ff53e-156a-4c03-9c9a-289b3bd26cfa"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "5bb2e996-7fc3-4f10-b73e-187ecd3610ed", "tool_call_id": "call_7c64e8168bb049869481cfb3", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:34:58.943188+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 44c1342a0dbb3d8743ad857a073164d6c396e4c5)", "id": "lc_7ebc9e48-8507-4fba-b510-bf941dfb679e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# ZAP Baseline Summary\n\nThis report is generated from `sample_data/zap_baseline.json` by\n`scripts/zap_json_to_markdown.py`.\n", "id": "lc_1bd43e77-48a8-4543-81c7-d82f215474bb"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "560fdc30-a2e8-429d-a489-aaae4eb21336", "tool_call_id": "call_7850f4dd27f44935b3647a9e", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:34:58.943210+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: f6f3a8a7367d2871c8cb070873313f49359cbd7b)", "id": "lc_a0633609-7704-4146-a289-b9eaf0a2911c"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"site\": [\n    {\n      \"@name\": \"http://127.0.0.1:8080\",\n      \"alerts\": [\n        {\n          \"pluginid\": \"10020\",\n          \"alert\": \"Missing Anti-clickjacking Header\",\n          \"riskdesc\": \"Medium (High)\",\n          \"desc\": \"Sample baseline finding for local demo app.\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n", "id": "lc_2f710e6a-73c1-4e4e-aa2e-09fd176ba3bc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "5565ca22-de8b-42a4-a0cf-c205285a1f36", "tool_call_id": "call_883db45783f74d1283a957a9", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:34:58.943306+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 5698261de2f81c2b7ed6ef350377c06079037a38)", "id": "lc_23a8b113-6fc7-4228-bfa0-a5963a4396ce"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\n\ndata = json.loads(Path('sample_data/zap_baseline.json').read_text())\nrows = []\nfor site in data.get('site', []):\n    for alert in site.get('alerts', []):\n        rows.append(f\"| {alert['pluginid']} | {alert['alert']} | {alert['riskdesc']} |\")\n\nout = Path('reports/baseline_summary.md')\nout.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\nout.write_text(\n    '# ZAP Baseline Summary\\n\\n'\n    '| Rule | Alert | Risk |\\n'\n    '| --- | --- | --- |\\n'\n    + '\\n'.join(rows) + '\\n'\n)\nprint(out)\n", "id": "lc_7e73a00f-31b0-4703-8701-9d09394089ea"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "47817523-4fa2-4641-aa0f-b6945d4e1fdc", "tool_call_id": "call_1cec7d4c1a6d4f7797c46d2b", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
